Kericho County is set to establish a lands registry where landowners will easily be getting title deeds.The proposed registry will be funded from part of the Sh.6.1 billion budget the county government approved last Thursday. The Huduma centre is where landowners could easily be helped get land documents freely just the same way those seeking national identity cards Kenya Revenue Authority(KRA) pin and other vital documents were getting currently,' speaker Japheth Mitai said.The proposed land registry is expected to help fight land grabbing.